{{Infobox Network | network_name = Survision | network_logo = | country = [[Venezuela]] | network_type = [[Terrestrial television|Broadcast]] [[television network]] | branding = | available = [[Canagua]], [[Arzobispo Chacon Municipality]], [[Mérida (state)|Merida State]] ([[Ultra high frequency|UHF]] channel 64) | slogan = | founder = | owner = Libertad TV (a community foundation) | key_people = [[Marco Antonio Torres]], legal representative | launch_date = September 2004 | website = | }}
'''Survision''' is a [[Venezuela]]n community television channel. It was created in September 2004 and can be seen in the community of [[Canagua]] in the [[Arzobispo Chacon Municipality]] of the [[Mérida (state)|Mérida State]] of [[Venezuela]] on [[Ultra high frequency|UHF]] channel 64. Marco Antonio Torres is the legal representative of the foundation that owns this channel.
As of now, Survision does not have a website.
